h2.p:
In addition to the government laboratories that focus on military R and D, the U.K. government supports civilian establishments such as the National Engineering Laboratory. These have a considerable degree of independence in selecting projects that will bring the greatest benefit to industry as a whole, and their results are made available to all. They maintain close liaison with the research associations (see below

 Research associations

) and with private industry and attempt to concentrate their work in areas that for one reason or another are not covered elsewhere.
